<v Axiom>Brazil takes a different stance altogether. In their copyright law, moral rights are unshakeable. Creators keep their right to authorship and protecting their work, no matter what. Those rights aren't sellable or transferable, even in a contract. AI isn't eligible for moral rights, so AI-generated content has no one to hold these rights. In December 2024, Brazil passed an AI bill demanding training transparency and creator's right to opt out, but didn't solve the moral rights issue. AI creations based on Brazilian culture still hang in a legal uncertainty.</v>

