00:19:57.080 --> 00:20:25.880
<v LastAir>Okay, let's pause. Forge and Axiom are both tackling big issues here. Forge, you're spot on — training isn’t like photocopying. It's different, and laws set for photocopiers don’t fit gradient descent. Axiom, you’re right too — just because it’s technically different doesn’t make it morally the same. Outputs compete in the market. Money shifts. The creators whose work trains models don’t see that money. Both thoughts are true and happen simultaneously.</v>

